column1: # SOURCE: Derived from wind_turbines-research.csv and daily_weather_openfield-research.csv
# DESCRIPTION: Daily wind energy output per turbine for small/medium/large distributed-scale turbines

# LOGIC: Wind speed extrapolated from 10m to hub height using power law (alpha=0.14). Power curve: P = P_rated * (v^3 - v_cin^3) / (v_rated^3 - v_cin^3) for v_cin <= v <= v_rated; P_rated for v_rated < v <= v_cout; 0 otherwise. Expected power computed by numerical integration of power curve over Rayleigh distribution of sub-daily wind speeds (corrects Jensen's inequality bias from using daily mean directly). System losses (availability

# ASSUMPTIONS: (1) Power-law wind shear exponent 0.14 for open coastal terrain. (2) Sub-daily wind speed variability modeled via Rayleigh distribution (sigma = v_mean * sqrt(2/pi)). (3) No air density correction for altitude/temperature.
